**FINDINGS**

1. [src/solver/arrow_schur.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/solver/arrow_schur.rs:725), [src/solver/arrow_schur.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/solver/arrow_schur.rs:773), [src/solver/latent_inner.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/solver/latent_inner.rs:198), [src/solver/persistent_warm_start.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/solver/persistent_warm_start.rs:398)  
Severity: definitive.

Wrong expression: the IFT predictor solves with cached factors documented as `H_tt^(i) + ridge_t·I`, then applies:
```rust
let v = chol_solve_vector(&self.htt_factors[i], &rhs);
```
and `LatentInnerSolver` can build the final cache with:
```rust
ridge_t.max(1e-12)
```

Correct expression: IFT requires the undamped Hessian:
```text
Δt_i = -(H_tt^(i))^{-1} (H_tβ^(i) Δβ + δg_t^(i))
```
not `(H_tt^(i) + λI)^{-1}`. Derivation: at the inner optimum,
`g_t^(i)(t_i*, β, ρ)=0`; differentiating gives
`H_tt^(i) dt_i + H_tβ^(i) dβ + δg_t^(i)=0`.

2. [src/solver/riemannian.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/solver/riemannian.rs:660), [src/solver/riemannian.rs](/Users/user/gam/src/solver/riemannian.rs:699)  
Severity: definitive.

Wrong expression:
```rust
let mut xi = solve_symmetric_tikhonov(&hess_r, &grad_r);
```
where `solve_symmetric_tikhonov` makes the full ambient matrix PD via:
```rust
a[[i, i]] += lambda;
```

Correct expression: solve only on the tangent space, e.g.
```text
(Qᵀ H_R Q + μI) η = -Qᵀ grad_R,   ξ = Qη
```
for tangent basis `Q`, or equivalently pin only the normal block:
```text
(H_R + αP_N + μP_T) ξ = -grad_R
```
The ambient `H_R` is singular in normal directions by construction; that normal nullspace is representational, not negative curvature. Current code therefore introduces artificial tangent damping even when `step.ridge == 0`.
